Why For Women

   Women typically live longer and we’re paid less. Shouldn’t we use
   financial tools created for us?

It was time to do better.

   Sallie Krawcheck served as CEO of Merrill Lynch Wealth Management and
   Smith Barney. It was through this experience that she realized that the
   “by men, for men” investing industry hasn’t worked very well for women.
   And that it has cost us the money to plan our futures and live the
   lives we want.
   Learn More
   Sallie Krawcheck

